snippet.textDisplay:
As a kid in the 80s, I used to love chitterlings, but then I saw em go straight from a living hog to the frying pan.

My grandad had a hog farm and he and my dad went out and killed a hog to eat. They strung him up by the hind feet, then gutted him.

My grandma picked up the intestines, cut em from the hog and sh*t just flowed out of them.

As a child, needless you say, that did something to me and I never ate chitterlings again or much hog at all, afterwards.

I wasn't squeamish. I could watch a cow go to slaughter and still eat it, but I didn't know chitterlings were basically a literal sh*tbag. 🤢🤮
